description: Demolition of existing buildings on site and construction of a mixed use scheme comprising 338 sq m of commercial /employment space (A1-A5, B1 or D1) and 165 residential flats arranged in 2 wings around a courtyard (69 x one-bed, 88 x two-bed, 5 x three-bed & 3 x four-bed units). The heights of the proposal vary from 4 to 7 storeys (plus galleries) including a lower ground /basement floor level. The scheme contains 37 car parking spaces and private and shared gardens for the residents. Departure from London Borough of Islington UDP 2002 Policies Env21, Env22 and Env23.
decision_conditions: REASON: The proposal due to its siting would result in an unacceptable loss of part of a Grade I Nature Conservation Area and is contrary to policies Env21 and Env22 of the adopted London Borough of Islington Unitary Development Plan (2002).
